  "body": "This issue just came up on IRC:  http://is.gd/1tSN42\n\nThe error mesage:\n\n```\n<anon>:17:5: 17:29 error: function calls in constants are limited to struct and enum constructors [E0015]\n<anon>:17     Instruction::new(4, nop),\n              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n```\n\nIs confusing - in this instance the user assumed (coming from other languages) that new was a constructor and should be allowed. In addition, struct constructors are not syntactically similar to function calls, so it is confusing to mention them in the error message. A better message would be something like \"function calls are not permitted in constants\", without the extra hint.\n",
